From 9fa2a3dd00a0fdbcc649c1f1ec74d4628fc8767b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sergey Fedorov <barracuda@macos-powerpc.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 19:37:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 07/13] toml: support nested arrays, full escape set, and
 line-ending backslash

The streaming TOML parser only accepted plain strings inside arrays and
only \" \\ \n in strings. Modern Cargo.tomls hit both limits:
- `package.metadata.deb.assets = [["path", "usr/bin/", "755"], ...]`
  (arrays of arrays; oxipng 10.1.1, ripgrep 15.2.0) - now parsed
  recursively; inline tables inside arrays are consumed and stored as an
  empty list (they only appear in sections minicargo ignores)
- `extended-description = """\` (line-ending backslash continuation) -
  now trims following whitespace per the TOML spec; also adds the
  remaining standard escapes (\b \t \f \r \uXXXX \UXXXXXXXX)

Verified: both crates' real manifests now load fully in minicargo.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_011M9MvswSD3mEeJcBm6S8z7
